race.description: Gooree Park Wines Country Boosted (C1) Handicap
race.comment: BRAVE XENA (6) made a sustained run from near the tail to get up and score convincingly on debut over 1100m at Nowra last start. Has to convert that heavy track form to a firmer surface today but deserves the benefit of any doubt. BOSCO (1) strolled to victory in a Moruya maiden two back then raced just off the speed and was beaten under two lengths in a BM58 over 1100m at Goulburn last time. Should appreciate the extra 100m now. Very fit and is a key contender. WOLF BAY (3) turned in a fair performance at Dubbo recently when returning from a 16-month absence. Will take a lot from that hit-out and the extra 200m today is ideal. STATE OF GRACE (10) is deep into her prep and still racing well. Found 1000m a bit sharp at Dubbo last time. Nicely drawn and can improve over this more favourable journey. THE GIT UP (8) hit form at Orange last start, albeit on a heavy track. Has placed seven from nine at this distance but is better with the sting out of the ground. Monitor track conditions.
